race.comment: COSMIC (11) jumped out strongly and then first-up she didn't have the best of it beaten 1L at Donald over 1620m. Draws awkwardly again but she has more up the sleeve and will be tough to beat. FIERCE FIGHTER (4) peaks off solid placings, with the latest at Werribee over a mile. Maps well and is sure to keep improving for an elite stable. Has the blinkers on after two runs without. ZETHEROS (10) went much better at Werribee and will be better for it. Has an inside gate today, and the step up to the mile is sure to suit. In the mix. WHERE EAGLES DARE (9) resumes over a mile at Terang at monster odds and was only beaten 2L after settling last in the 13-horse field. Has the inside gate today and deserves consideration on the back of that effort.
